The Vice President of the United States, Joe Biden, congratulates the Nigerian people and their leaders on the peaceful democratic election. He commends both President Goodluck Jonathan and President-elect Muhammadu Buhari for their statesmanship in leading their supporters through this historic vote. Biden praises Jonathan for conceding defeat graciously, which strengthens the country he has led. He recognizes the challenges that the next Nigerian government will face in fighting corruption and terrorism and promoting inter-communal peace. The US looks forward to working closely with President-elect Buhari to advance their shared interest in Nigeria's success.